---
title: Fragrant Indonesian Style Veggie Curry with King Prawns with Courgette, Green Beans and Basmati Rice
description: They grow a lot of coconuts in Indonesia and love to cook with them. The country's food is often spicy but the heat is offset with sweetness from the coconuts and often a sour note too. We're attempting this balancing act in today's curry. The sauce bathing the veggies should be hot, sharp and sweet. Top it all off with golden toasted peanuts.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/thai-style-veggie-yellow-curry-with-king-prawns-f2a08e8d-0451f96e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/fragrant-indonesian-style-veggie-curry-with-king-prawns-619f4756f6e92f4622685d15-314a8cff.pdf
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/fragrant-indonesian-style-veggie-curry-with-king-prawns-619f4756f6e92f4622685d15
cuisine: Indonesian
course: main course
author: Mimi Morley
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 725 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 85 g
