  sodium: 4.9 g
  serving size: 650
---

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks. Trim the @courgette{1}, then halve lengthways. Slice into 1cm wide half moons. Trim the @green beans{150%g} and chop in half. Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}. Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}.

Pour the cold @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a #tightfitting lid{}. Stir in the @Basmati rice{150%g}, @star anise{1} and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cover with the lid and bring to the boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling, turn the heat down to its lowest setting. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Heat a #large frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the peanuts and dry-fry until toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily. Once toasted, pop them into a #small bowl{} and set aside.

Pop the (now empty) pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle}. Add the onion and stir-fry until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @ginger puree{1%tsp} and @yellow Thai style paste{45%g} along with a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more. Add the green beans, pepper and courgette, then stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @water for the sauce{75%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Reduce the heat and simmer until the curry has thickened and the vegetables are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When the curry is cooked, stir through the @soy sauce{15%ml} and add a squeeze of lime juice. Taste and add more lime juice if needed. Remove the star anise from the rice, fluff it up with a #fork{} then stir through the lime zest.

When everything is ready, serve the rice in #bowls{} with the Thai style veggie curry on top. Finish by sprinkling over the toasted peanuts. Enjoy!

> STEP 5 MOD: If you've added prawns to your recipe, when the curry is cooked, stir in the @king prawns{150%g} and cook for another ~{3-4%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle. Continue with the step as instructed.